The [add-to-app documentation](https://docs.flutter.dev/development/add-to-app/android/project-setup) specifies that it makes sense to set `abiFilters` ("Doing this avoids a missing libflutter.so runtime crash") - I wonder if it wouldn't make sense to also add this to the [default app template](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/master/packages/flutter_tools/templates/app_shared/android-kotlin.tmpl/app/build.gradle.tmpl) of flutter itself? Are there any downsides to use this `abiFilters` for standard flutter apps?

```gradle
android {
  //...
  defaultConfig {
    ndk {
      // Filter for architectures supported by Flutter.
      abiFilters 'armeabi-v7a', 'arm64-v8a', 'x86_64'
    }
  }
}
```

